properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 7 at 2:07PM PST until February 10 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Lake Wind Advisory, northeast winds 10 to 20
mph with gusts up to 40 mph expected. Waves 2 to 4 feet. For
the Wind Advisory, northeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up
to 50 mph expected.

* WHERE...Greater Lake Tahoe Area.

* WHEN...For the Lake Wind Advisory, from 10 AM Saturday to 10
AM PST Sunday. For the Wind Advisory, from 10 AM Sunday to 4
AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Some trees may get blown over Sunday or Sunday night due to the
unusual direction of this northeast wind.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Small boats, kayaks and paddle boards will
be prone to capsizing and should remain off lake waters until
conditions improve. Highest waves are expected on the western
shores.
properties.instruction:
Now is the time to secure loose outdoor items such as patio
furniture, decorations, and trash cans before winds increase
which could blow these items away. The best thing to do is prepare
ahead of time by making sure you have extra food and water on
hand, flashlights with spare batteries and/or candles in the event
of a power outage.
